<h1>Editing User, using HTML POST</h1>
<form action="/users/<%= @user.id %>" method="patch" attribute="accept-charset='UTF-8'">
  <input type="hidden" name="authenticity_token" value="<%= form_authenticity_token %>">

  <label for="username">User name: </label>
  <input id="username" type="text" name="user[username]" value=<%= @user.username %>>
  <br/>

  <label for="email">E-mail: </label>
  <input id="email" type="email" name="user[email]" value=<%= @user.email %>>
  <br/>

  <label for="password">Password: </label>
  <input id="password" type="password" name="user[password]">
  <br/>

  <input type="submit" value="Edit User"> <br>
</form>
<br/>
<hr/>

<h2>Renders the FORM_WITH</h2>
<p>This is pretty good, because it automatically realizes that the verb is PATCH instead of POST. The HTML version above had to be tweaked.</p>
